entries.femaleVariant: Judy Alvarez. I'd say it's great to see you but I've never been one to lie.
Thought you'd hit rock bottom when you joined the Mox.
Consorting with a persona who is very non grata…
You somehow never fail to lower my expectations.
Did what I had to do.
Came to Clouds for info, left with info.
Called me a murderer. You're right – I killed Woodman. I'd do it again in a heartbeat.
entries.maleVariant: Call me a murderer? You're right – I killed Woodman. I'd do it again in a heartbeat.

entries.femaleVariant: Judy wants to make you a proposition.
Judy has a proposal... about Clouds.
Ever heard of a little something called "compromise"? Should try it sometime.
Wanna come back? Done. Always valued your skills, you know that. Just don't get why you had to drag this... loose end in here.
Had enough.
Don't mind me – here to blend into the furniture.
Left a lasting impression. Good.
Ah, don't mind me – just here to blend into the decor.
entries.maleVariant: Don't mind me – just here to blend into the decor.

entries.femaleVariant: Guess I left a lasting impression. Good.
entries.maleVariant: Heh, guess I left a lasting impression. Good.

entries.femaleVariant: You two done bickering over diddly squat?
That all you're good at – blowin' hot air?
Urgh, sure ask a lot of questions.
Judy's idea – think about it. Could work.
Well, can't ever rule violence out.
That's no reason. Why come at all?
My job, among other things, is to remember unsavory customers. Naturally, I take it upon myself to deal with them, too.
A pathetic attempt at getting under my skin.
Gonna pretend as if you two weren't ever here. For old times' sake, Judy.
'Cause if you are, I'd like to get down to biz.
Heh, this is a waste of our time. Come on, we'll get by without 'er.
entries.maleVariant: Huh, this is a waste of our time. Come on, we'll get by without 'er.

entries.femaleVariant: We're not done talkin'. But you'd do well to hear Judy out, or we'll make sure your worst fear comes true.
entries.maleVariant: Oh, we're not done talking. But you'd do well to hear Judy out, or we'll make sure your worst fears come true.

entries.femaleVariant: Jude, be sure to gimme a call once you're done mourning and wanna get back to reality.
I'm leavin'.
Smart move.
Guess you've managed to stoop even lower, now.
Consorting with a common thug…
To make sure Judy gets what she came for.
Just what exactly are you after?
Gonna go and harass another doll?
Compromises take time I just don't have.
Jude woulda had a better chance without you.
Paid you one visit and you remember me?
Now, how'm I to deal with you?
What happened in between is what happens when people refuse to work with you.
Here's the thing – literally in moments security'll figure out you're here. Got two options – go out the way you came in, or get thrown out.
And don't get me wrong, Jude. I'd gladly sit and catch up. Been quite a while since we last talked.
But you're not safe here at Clouds. Especially not with her at your side.
entries.maleVariant: But you're not safe here at Clouds. Especially not with him at your side.

entries.femaleVariant: Stop treatin' dolls like meat and I'll consider it. But first things first – Clouds needs to be taken from the Tyger Claws.
Startin' to think blowin' hot air's all you're good at.
Yes, V – I mean you.
OK, look. It's clear what happened to Ev was… traumatic.
OK, since you seem more reasonable, care to explain what this is about?
Literally moments from now security's gonna figure out you're here. Got two options – go out the way you came in, or get thrown out.
And that's not a threat or figure of speech. Just a friendly heads up.
We're not done talking. Hear Judy out.
Wouldn't rule it out.
Yeesh, you've always been unstable.
What's next? Threats?
Waste of time, this.
First you settle for the Mox, now murderers. I shudder to think what's next.
Also I never liked surprise parties, which you know.
Huh? I was convinced you didn't know.
That girl was askin' for an unhappy ending. I was just surprised it took so long.
And if I'd known what he did to Evelyn when she needed help, I wouldn't've have gone so easy on him.
Oh? Stand to lose my youth, eddies and influence?
Something's gonna happen. But you'll be the last to know.
Huh.
Gotta liberate Clouds, take over.
We need you.
We need you. Can't do what we wanna do... without you.
entries.maleVariant: We need you. We can't do what we wanna do... without you.

entries.femaleVariant: Wanna tear Clouds outta the Tyger Claws' paws. Dolls should own it, control it.
All right... this has been fun and all, but... I think it's time you got going.
We gotta do something! Or everyone'll end up like Evie. Woodman raped her while she was unconscious, then sold her like she was so much scrap.
Mess with the Claws, blowback'll hit every one of the dolls in here.
So, not willing to help?
So, you won't help.
I thought I expressed myself clearly.
You mean making better life choices?
We wanna help the dolls.
Dolls make more eddies than anyone else in the industry. Thanks to the chip, they experience no trauma. Every whore in Night City wants to work here.
It's the Tyger Claws that're the problem, and people like Woodman. He raped Evelyn while she was unconscious, then sold her off like so much scrap.
What you two're out to do is... impossible. Completely beyond your means.
You seem a bundle of nerves.
I've a mind to kill the bastards with my bare hands.
So yeah... you could say I'm a teensy bit nervous.
I'm ready, let's go.
I'm ready, let's go.
Gotta know where to lead the convo.
Am I here as your huscle?
How you aim to bring her around?
Tell me anything more about her?
You nervous?
So, in brief, I'm just here as your huscle, right?
Never said that. I just know the woman better.
Care to be a bit more specific? Wouldn't mind knowing what to expect.
Expect everything. Miss a beat, she'll wrap you 'round her finger, get you on her agenda while thinkin' you're the one in control.
Hm... Heh, guess I know the type.
entries.maleVariant: Ooh, huh... Guess I know the type.

entries.femaleVariant: How you aim to get her over to our side?
By tellin' the truth. About Evelyn – what happened and why.
Think that'll cut it?
No. Have to improvise from there.
Some detes about her could be useful, when I talk to her, don't you think?
No, leave the talkin' to me.
Talkin' with Maiko's like a game of 3D chess – don't let her derail you.
Hold on. I'll open it.
You've used this entrance before?
Know how to get around their systems?
Looks like you've come this way before. More'n once.
entries.maleVariant: Looks like you've come this way before. More than once.

entries.femaleVariant: Hm. I have, on occasion.
Easy as paella.
Come on, let's go.
Follow me.
Lock like that – no way you cracked it open on your first try.
entries.maleVariant: A lock like that? No way you cracked it open on your first try.

entries.femaleVariant: Know how to get around their systems?
entries.maleVariant: You know how to get around their systems?

entries.femaleVariant: Appears so. Was hopin' they hadn't run any updates since I left.
Looks like I was right.
Hey, V. Thanks for showin'.
A Clouds employee took advantage of Evelyn.
Judy's proposal – give it some thought.
Well, well, Jude. See you've found a true and loyal fan.
Shouldn't be workin' here, then.
You aware what Woodman did to Evelyn when she was desperate for help? You sit by, let that happen?
Doesn't make you wonder why you even work here?
entries.maleVariant: Doesn't it make you wonder why you even work here?

entries.femaleVariant: And so you don't think I'm brushing you off completely... Forrest'll be on the maintenance level in a couple minutes. Alone.
Tyger Claw bosses rule this place. Know how much I mean to them?
About as much as you two and your problems mean to me. Read, negligible.
This is a waste of time.
This is a waste of time.
You chose the wrong side.
I'm not your enemy here.
You picked the wrong side, Maiko.
I'm not your enemy here.
Sounds like I left a mark on this place. Good.
Came to Clouds for info, left with info.
Appreciate it. Now what exactly are you after?
All the while, I did my best to make sure no one standing in my way ended up in a garbage bag.
I'll be the judge of that.
And I didn't ask for your opinion.
If by "mark" you mean buckets o' blood, then yeah – congrats.
[Wait]
Yup, bet I even know why.
